Create a GitHub Pages-ready repo with a single-file static site.

Requirements:
- Put the full chatbot code into /index.html (I will paste it).
- Add a /README.md explaining what it is and how to deploy on GitHub Pages.
- No build tools, no frameworks, no dependencies.
- Ensure the site loads locally by opening index.html in a browser.
- Ensure GitHub Pages works from root.

Optional nice-to-haves:
- Add a simple LICENSE (MIT).
- Add a basic .gitignore (even though no build artifacts).
